# Naritsa - Research portfolio

This repository collects my public work on epistemic safety, body-worn cameras, ontological hygiene, and related topics. Each folder in `/works` links to an open-access version on Zenodo.

## Works

- [Epistemic scanning and scanfield](works/epistemic-scanning/)  
  Framework for how questions and prompts "scan" people in dark-forest social environments.
  https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.17993169

- [Body-worn cameras and accountability](works/bodycams-accountability/)  
  Why bodycam footage needs independent custody and cryptographic integrity, not just "transparency" rhetoric.
  https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.17993162

- [Ontological hygiene meta-test](works/ontological-hygiene/)  
  Treating high-impact concepts like critical infrastructure, with a stress-test for categories.
  https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.17993135

- [Peak-transplants and invasive species](works/peak-transplants/)  
  Reframing species introductions as moving evolved peaks between landscapes.
  https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.17993139

## Elsewhere

